7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Crowdin and Phrase (Memsource) share a solid foundation of core features including Machine Translation, Translation Memory, Glossary, Api Access. Where Crowdin pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Real Time, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Phrase (Memsource) uniquely offers Custom Models, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Crowdin holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Phrase (Memsource) scores 8/10 overall and 6/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Crowdin offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to Phrase (Memsource)'s starting price of $25/mo. Crowdin has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. Phrase (Memsource) does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
