b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Crowdin is best suited for open source projects, game developers, community translation, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Phrase (Memsource), meanwhile, shines for localization teams, translation agencies, product teams, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2009, Crowdin describes itself as \"Collaborative localization platform with crowdsourcing and AI translation.\" Phrase (Memsource), established in 2010, positions itself as \"AI-powered translation management system for localization workflows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Phrase (Memsource)** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0). However, this does not mean Crowdin is a poor choice — far from it. Crowdin excels in its own right, particularly for open source projects and game developers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value comprehensive tms with strong cat tools, go with Phrase (Memsource). If great crowdsourcing capabilities matters more to you, Crowdin is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
